Negated Value Matching

Source: R/dev_utils.R
dev_util_notin.Rd

Returns a logical vector indicating if there is no match of the left operand in the right operand.

Usage

x %notin% table

Arguments

x

The values to be matched

table

The values to be matched against

Author

Thomas Neitmann

Examples

`%notin%` <- admiral:::`%notin%`
"a" %notin% c("b", "v", "k")
#> [1] TRUE
